ecute the script end-to-end against test/staging data endpoints and a real email delivery path to a test mailbox. Assert message arrival for configured recipient and basic report integrity (expected sections present) in the received email.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"System is required because the assertion is inbox delivery over real infrastructure; lower-level tests with mocked email would miss real transport failures.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.62,"Agentic":0.22,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This behavior crosses process/time boundaries (scheduled rerun) plus persistent filesystem state and real delivery endpoint reachability. Real failure often appears only across actual runs with persisted spool/retry artifacts; pure in-process mocks can miss path, locking, serialization, or invocation-boundary issues. Rejected Agentic/Workflow: retry logic does not depend on model-output quality or multi-agent decisions.","test_description":"Run the script in two real invocations: first with email endpoint intentionally unreachable, assert fallback file is written; second invocation with delivery restored, assert queued report is sent and retry artifact is cleared/marked delivered.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"System level matches required subprocess-like scheduled-run boundary and real file persistence behavior.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.7,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.03}}]}
